21 January 2011The Minister of Social Development, Ms Bathabile Dlamini, will on Saturday, 22 January 2011, meet with stakeholders from business and civil society. The aim of the meeting is to discuss ways of collaboration with the view of lobbying business and civil society to provide relief and assistance to victims of the flood disaster across the country. This is part of government's efforts to mobilise various stakeholders to assist people affected by the recent floods. The Minister will address a press conference on the outcomes of the meeting at a briefing to be held as follows: Date: Sunday, 23 January 2011 Time: 9am Venue: Union Buildings, Room 153 Note: There will be a video link-up to Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Cape Town. RSVP: Proffesor Ndawonde Cell: 078 456 5738 Enquiries: Thapelo Sakoana Cell: 078 453 6750 Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)